        "behavior": "; 74573 — octal D-type transparent latch, 3-state, non-inverting. Derived\n; from the function table (datasheet Table 3):\n;   /OE  LE   Dn        Qn\n;    L   H    L / H     L / H     transparent: output follows data\n;    L   L    (l / h)   L / H     latched: holds the value from before LE fell\n;    H   X    X         Z         outputs high-Z; latch state unaffected\n;\n; TRANSPARENT-LATCH CONVENTION (FR-079d): a transparent latch is level-\n; sensitive, not edge-clocked, so it has NO clock: pin. Each output is a .L\n; latch output loaded from Dn, made transparent by a single-term .G gate. The\n; latch follows Dn while its .G term is true and holds when the term is false.\n; Here LE is the active-HIGH latch-enable pin, so the gate is simply \"LE\": the\n; latch is transparent while LE is HIGH and holds when LE is LOW.\n;\n; Equations are physical-level GALasm: '/' is the complement operator and\n; signal names are this file's pin names with any active-low '/' prefix\n; dropped (pin /OE is GAL signal OE, so '/OE' below means \"pin /OE is LOW\").\n; Each Qn is a transparent-latch output (.L) loaded from Dn, gated open by\n; .G = LE, and driven through a single-term tristate enable (.E) that drives\n; the pin only while /OE is LOW; when /OE is HIGH the .E term is false and Qn\n; is high-impedance, covering the disabled rows of the function table.\nQ0.L = D0\nQ0.G = LE\nQ0.E = /OE\nQ1.L = D1\nQ1.G = LE\nQ1.E = /OE\nQ2.L = D2\nQ2.G = LE\nQ2.E = /OE\nQ3.L = D3\nQ3.G = LE\nQ3.E = /OE\nQ4.L = D4\nQ4.G = LE\nQ4.E = /OE\nQ5.L = D5\nQ5.G = LE\nQ5.E = /OE\nQ6.L = D6\nQ6.G = LE\nQ6.E = /OE\nQ7.L = D7\nQ7.G = LE\nQ7.E = /OE\n",
        "description": "Octal D-type transparent latch, active-high latch enable, 3-state",
        "datasheet": {
